english:
  title: Seeing Off Ju Jaran
  author: Cho Seo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The world shines with civility and grace—all heaven and earth at peace.
    The aging are honored, granted safe return to life.
    The Min Mountains guard the path in emerald green,
    the boat turns back where the Chu waters run clear.

    The zither and books await you with purpose,
    flowers and trees will bloom again in splendor.
    Yet here I am, restless and uneasy—
    why do I linger, hesitating as I see you depart?
  footnotes:
    - The Min Mountains (民山) and Chu waters (楚水) reference the regions of Sichuan and the Yangtze River valley, suggesting a journey southward through classical Chinese landscape.
    - The zither (琴) and books (書) represent the scholarly and artistic pursuits awaiting the traveler's retirement.
    - The poem's final turn reveals an emotional undercurrent beneath the formal language of farewell—the speaker's own uncertainty masks a deeper reluctance to part.
